# Agent Memory

Use `mem` CLI (via Shell) for persistent memory across sessions.

## Before starting any task
- `mem search "<relevant query>"` — check for prior knowledge (searches all groups)

## After resolving incidents or learning something new
- `mem add "<name>" "<what was learned>" --group-id incidents`

## Commands
- `mem search "<query>"` — search all facts and relationships across all groups
- `mem search "<query>" --group-id incidents` — search within a specific group
- `mem add "<name>" "<body>" [--group-id <id>]` — store knowledge
- `mem episodes [--last-n 5]` — recent context
- `mem status` — health check

## Group IDs (use with --group-id on add)
- `incidents` — on-call incident resolutions
- `infrastructure` — hardware, networking, cluster knowledge
- `design` — architecture and design decisions
- `together-ops` — general operations (default for add)
